<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2634] IndexReader.isCurrent() lies if documents were only removed by latest commit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2634</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Usecase is as following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Get indexReader via indexWriter.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Delete documents by Term via indexWriter. &lt;br/&gt;
3. Commit indexWriter.&lt;br/&gt;
4. indexReader.isCurrent() returns true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Usually there is a check if index reader is current. If not then it is reopened (re-obtained via writer or ect.). But this causes the problem when documents can still be found through the search after deletion.&lt;br/&gt;
Testcase is attached.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 9.10&lt;br/&gt;
Sun-java-jdk 1.6.0_20-b02&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
